2026-05-17 | Make Array Beautiful

	Question
Return final beautiful array.
	Key Insight
This behaves exactly like:
		pair cancellation problems  
A stack efficiently simulates removals.
	Approach
1.	Create empty stack/vector  
2.	Traverse array:
		let current = x  
3.	If stack top and current have opposite signs:
		remove top
		do not insert current  
4.	Otherwise:
		push current  
5.	Return remaining elements.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> makeBeautiful(vector<int>& arr) {
        vector<int> st;
        for(int x : arr){
            if(!st.empty()){
                int top = st.back();
                // opposite signs
                if((top >= 0 && x < 0) ||
                   (top < 0 && x >= 0)){
                    st.pop_back();
                    continue;
                }
            }
            st.push_back(x);
        }
        return st;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Whenever opposite signs appear adjacent:
		they disappear together  
A stack naturally handles:
		repeated chain removals efficiently.
